  "text": "[4] defines the \"Provable Data Possession\" (PDP) model for ensuring possession of files on untrusted storages. It utilizes RSA-based homomorphic tags to audit the outsourced data, thus can provide public verifiability. Unfortunately, dynamic data storage is not considered. If the scheme from static data storage is extended directly to dynamic case, there are many design and security problems. In [CITATION_1] [24], they propose a dynamic version of the prior PDP scheme. However, the number of queries is limited and fully dynamic data operations is not supported, i.e., block insertions cannot be supported. In our work, we support fully data dynamics including block insertion, block deletion and block modification. Our scheme fits not only for static data verification but also for dynamic data verification.",
